data.text:
Eligibility Remaining: 2024, 2025

Honors & Awards

2023 Fall SEC Academic Honor Roll

2023 Goodyear Cotton Bowl Classic Defensive MVP

2023 (Redshirt Junior): Appeared in all 13 games on the year, cracking the starting lineup all but once ... Racked up 43 tackles, 25 of which were solo, in addition to 8.5 tackles for loss and five sacks ... his nine quarterback hurries were the most on the team ... His five sacks on the campaign bests his previous career total in three seasons ... Notched a career-high six tackles, 1.5 tackles for loss and a sack in the home opener against South Dakota (Aug. 31) ... Recorded five tackles, a tackle for loss and sack in thrilling victory over Kansas State (Sept. 16) ... Matched his tackling career high three weeks later with a performance that featured six tackles, 1.5 tackles for loss and a sack in the victory over Memphis in St. Louis (Sept. 23) ... Claimed his first career forced fumble against Memphis ... had a career-high two tackles for loss and a sack in road victory over Kentucky (Oct. 14) ... Picked up his second career forced fumble during a three tackle performance in a homecoming match up with South Carolina (Oct. 21).

2022 (Redshirt Sophomore): Saw action in six games this season … Finished the season with seven total tackles, two tackles-for-loss and two sacks … Had a three-tackle outing in the bowl game against Wake Forest (12/23).

2021 (Redshirt Freshman): Appeared in seven games ... Made nine tackles on the year, including six solo stops and two sacks ... Recorded first career sack against SEMO (9/18) and added second against North Texas (10/9) ... Twice made three tackles in a game -- at Kentucky (9/11) and North Texas (10/9) … Had two tackles against New Mexico State (11/19).

2020 (Freshman): Redshirted the season.
